<subSubSection pageId="18" pageNumber="19" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="18.[818,1442,1428,1594]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[818,916,1428,1447]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Discussion</emphasis>
. Nests of this species have been found in the ground, and in sheltered above ground sites, such as hollow trees, wall voids, and attics. A queen of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Smith" authorityYear="1868" box="[986,1095,1487,1506]" class="Insecta" family="Vespidae" genus="Vespa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="simillima">
<emphasis box="[986,1095,1487,1506]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">V. simillima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was found in the village of Tsaochan in 
<collectingCountry box="[842,910,1516,1535]" name="Taiwan" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Taiwan</collectingCountry>
in 2003, but it is unclear whether the species has established on the island (
<bibRefCitation author="Sung" box="[1019,1175,1545,1565]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Sung" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" pagination="303 - 306" refId="ref13496" refString="Sung, I. - H., S. Yamane, and K. - K. Ho. 2006. A new record of a hornet from Taiwan. Formosan Entomol. 26: 303 - 306." type="journal article" year="2006">Sung et al. 2006</bibRefCitation>
). It is apparently not established in British 
<collectingCountry box="[967,1058,1575,1594]" name="Colombia" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Colombia</collectingCountry>
(Kimsey and Carpenter 2012).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
